sfsound concert new music with electronics events at stanford sfsound concert new music with electronics facebook twitter email print add to calendar drawing on an extraordinary roster of bay area musicians sfsoundgroup is the main performing group of the sfsoundseries the virtuoso sfsound instrumentalists are all composers in their own right offering a diverse range of talents including skilled improvisation performance art computer audio programming university level music scholarship instrument making didjeridu playing and styrofoam bowing sfsoundgroup comes to ccrma to present an evening of new and historical pieces for acoustic instruments with electronics here's the program for this evening program james tenney ergodos ii for john cage 1978 computer generated tape with instrumental responses phil niblock disseminate 1998 pre recorded and live instruments mario davidovsky synchronisms 3 1965 cello and tape per bloland quintet 2005 sax and live electronics kyle bruckmann cell structure 2009 oboe clarinet and recorded analog electronics matt ingalls false awakening 2008 amplified instruments and electronics performers kyle bruckmann oboe matt ingalls clarinet john ingle saxophone monica scott cello learn more about sfsound http sfsound org what sfsound concert when thursday february 2 2012 8pm where ccrma stage 3rd floor the knoll building 660 lomita drive stanford ca 94305 free admission map http goo gl eyova when thursday february 2 2012 8 00 pm approximate duration of 1.5 hour s where center for computer research in music and acoustics ccrma stage 3rd floor the knoll building 660 lomita drive stanford ca 94305 map audience general public faculty staff students alumni friends tags arts lecture reading music sponsor center for computer research in music and acoustics contact 6502658316 ruviaro ccrma stanford edu admission free permalink http events stanford edu events 304 30499 more info last modified january 20 2012
